  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Provision of Multi-Sectoral Assistance and Strengthening Social Cohesion for Refugees and the Host Community in Southeast Turkey</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">In response to the needs of Syrian refugees living within host communities, as well as the needs of the broader host community, through this project IOM is undertaking activities to rehabilitate public and community infrastructure in Turkey to facilitate access for refugees and host community members to essential services. The project also provides Syrian refugees and local Turkish youth with business skills and knowledge to support socio-economic resilience and self-reliance, while also supporting municipalities in implementing a model for integrated service delivery to refugees and other migrants, simultaneously promoting social cohesion with the host communities.</narrative>
  </description>
